In this statement, President Obama strongly condemns the shooting at the offices of Charlie Hebdo magazine in Paris, which resulted in the death of 12 people. He expresses his thoughts and prayers for the victims and the people of France. The President highlights the strong alliance between France and the United States in fighting against terrorists who threaten their shared security. He praises the French people for standing up for universal values and sees the city of Paris as a symbol of resilience against the attackers. The President assures that his administration is in contact with French officials and is ready to provide any necessary assistance in bringing the terrorists to justice.